    <p>Op­er­at­ing cash reg­is­ters, prod­uct scan­ners and pay­ment machines — that might come to mind when you think of a cashier's role. But it en­tails far more than just those. For starters, cashiers need to be able to work un­der pres­sure in the form of grow­ing lines and im­pa­tient cus­tomers, and will also need to ex­hibit the abil­ity to mul­ti­task and main­tain pa­tience.</p>
    <p>If you think you've got the req­ui­site traits, and would like to give cashier­ing a try, check out Class 789 for job de­tails</p>

